# Cursor Rules for react-synth

## TypeScript Style Guide

### Type Definitions

- Always use `type` instead of `interface` for all type definitions
- Use intersection types (`&`) instead of `extends` when composing types
- Prefer explicit type annotations for better IDE support

### Examples

✅ Correct:

```typescript
type UserProps = BaseProps & {
  name: string;
  age: number;
};

type Config = {
  apiUrl: string;
  timeout: number;
};
```

❌ Avoid:

```typescript
interface UserProps extends BaseProps {
  name: string;
  age: number;
}

interface Config {
  apiUrl: string;
  timeout: number;
}
```

## Architecture Principles

- Follow the "two clocks" scheduling pattern (JavaScript timer + Web Audio
  clock)
- All timing is beat-based, converted via `(beats * 60) / bpm`
- Components register callbacks rather than rendering DOM
- Use React context for passing audio/scheduling dependencies
